OL,3,CWhy might employers now be sued if
OL,4,Cthey don't take menopause seriously?
OL,6,FWords by Beth Thomas, ITV News
OL,7,Fjournalist
OL,9,FEmployers in England and Wales could
OL,10,Fbe sued for breaching equality laws if
OL,11,Fthey do not make "reasonable
OL,12,Fadjustments" for women going through
OL,13,Fmenopause under new guidance.
OL,15,FThe Equality and Human Rights
OL,16,FCommission (EHRC) said menopausal
OL,17,Fsymptoms that have a "long term and
OL,18,Fsubstantial impact" on a woman's
OL,19,Fability to carry out normal day-to-day
OL,20,Factivities "may be considered a
OL,21,Fdisability".
