OL,3,CWhy might employers now be sued if
OL,4,Cthey don't take menopause seriously?
OL,6,FAnyone who has a period will go
OL,7,Fthrough the menopause when it stops,
OL,8,Fwith symptoms normally beginning in
OL,9,Fthe mid-40s, but it can also happen
OL,10,Fearlier.
OL,12,FMenopause can cause symptoms like
OL,13,Fanxiety, mood swings, brain fog, hot
OL,14,Fflushes and irregular periods.
OL,16,FThe NHS recognises that these symptoms
OL,17,Fcan have a big impact on
OL,18,Frelationships, social lives, and work.
OL,20,FSymptoms can start years before
OL,21,Fperiods stop and carry on afterwards.
