OL,3,CWhy might employers now be sued if
OL,4,Cthey don't take menopause seriously?
OL,6,FBaroness Kishwer Falkner, the
OL,7,Fwatchdog's chairwoman, said the new
OL,8,Fguidance sets out legal obligations
OL,9,Ffor employers and provides advice on
OL,10,F"how they can best support their
OL,11,Fstaff."
OL,13,FIf menopause symptoms have a long term
OL,14,Fand substantial impact on a woman's
OL,15,Fability to carry out normal day-to-day
OL,16,Factivities, they may be considered a
OL,17,Fdisability, the watchdog says.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/13
