OL,3,CWhy might employers now be sued if
OL,4,Cthey don't take menopause seriously?
OL,6,FThe guidance also states that taking
OL,7,Fdisciplinary action against a
OL,8,Fmenopausal woman because of menopause-
OL,9,Frelated absence from work could amount
OL,10,Fto unlawful discrimination, unless it
OL,11,Fis justified.
OL,13,FUsing language that ridicules someone
OL,14,Fbecause of their menopausal symptoms
OL,15,Fcould be harassment.
OL,17,FUniform policies that disadvantage
OL,18,Fwomen with menopause symptoms could
OL,19,Falso amount to indirect sex, age, or
OL,20,Fdisability discrimination.
