OL,3,CWhy might employers now be sued if
OL,4,Cthey don't take menopause seriously?
OL,6,FWhile menopause isn't specifically
OL,7,Frecognised as a protected
OL,8,Fcharacteristic, employees experiencing
OL,9,Fit may be protected by discrimination
OL,10,Flaws relating to age, sex, disability
OL,11,Fand gender reassignment, as the new
OL,12,FEHRC guidance recognises.
OL,14,FUnder the Equality Act 2010, you are
OL,15,Fdisabled if you have a "physical or
OL,16,Fmental impairment that has a
OL,17,F'substantial' and 'long-term' negative
OL,18,Feffect on your ability to do normal
OL,19,Fdaily activities".
